sentence: Analysts at Goldman Sachs on Tuesday offered some positive commentary for home improvement warehouse operators The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ).
The firm said it boosted its earnings estimates for HD through 2012, noting the company is accelerating is share buyback program.
Goldman maintained its "Neutral" rating and $45 price target on HD, suggesting a 3.4% upside to the stock's Friday closing price of $43.51.
Meanwhile, Goldman maintained its "Buy" rating on LOW while boosting its price target to $29.
That new target suggests a 10% upside to LOW's Friday closing price of $26.32.
The firm also raised its earnings estimates for the company, citing expectations of better sales due to warmer weather.
Home Depot and Lowes shares both posted modest gains in premarket trading Tuesday following the analyst notes.
Shares of Home Depot ( HD ) have a 2.67% dividend yield, based on Friday's closing stock price of $43.51.
The stock has technical support in the $39-$40 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $45-$46 price levels.
Shares of Lowe's ( LOW ) have a 2.13% dividend yield, based on Friday's closing stock price of $26.32.
The stock has technical support in the $23-$24 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $27-$29 price levels.

The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ) are both currently rated "Neutral" by Dividend.com
